<span id="freeTextContainer18052333920641810357">Oh boy. I&apos;m not sure what to say other than I cannot think of one aspect I enjoyed about this book. I tend to gravitate toward dark, disturbing, and twisted stories (<s>what does that say about me???</s>), but this was just sad with no pay off. Each page felt like a chore to get through and I didn&apos;t even find the illustrations redeeming. I&apos;m clearly in the minority, but I may have possibly been bit by the old &quot;heard the story so many times that the original feels like a rip off&quot; bug. Definitely not my </span>
  <span id="freeText18052333920641810357" style="display:none">Oh boy. I'm not sure what to say other than I cannot think of one aspect I enjoyed about this book. I tend to gravitate toward dark, disturbing, and twisted stories (<s>what does that say about me???</s>), but this was just sad with no pay off. Each page felt like a chore to get through and I didn't even find the illustrations redeeming. I'm clearly in the minority, but I may have possibly been bit by the old "heard the story so many times that the original feels like a rip off" bug. Definitely not my cup of tea and I shall choose to bury my head in the sand and pretend this version does not exist. ;) The only reason I didn't DNF this was A) I'm trying my hardest to finish all my popsugar books if possible and B) I try not to DNF books under 200 pages if possible. Rant is over and now I'll move on to the next read!</span>
