    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_3458378013" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3458378013" />
    <a title="Valliya Rennell" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/58882300-valliya-rennell"><img alt="Valliya Rennell" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1613300912p2/58882300.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3458378013?book_show_action=true">Jan 11, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Valliya Rennell" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Valliya Rennell" href="/user/show/58882300-valliya-rennell">Valliya Rennell</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780147508652" href="/book/show/16101115-peter-pan">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/58882300-valliya-rennell?shelf=c-novel">c-novel</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/58882300-valliya-rennell?shelf=c-short-story">c-short-story</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/58882300-valliya-rennell?shelf=d-fantasy">d-fantasy</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/58882300-valliya-rennell?shelf=d-classic">d-classic</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/58882300-valliya-rennell?shelf=x-reviewed-books">x-reviewed-books</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/58882300-valliya-rennell?shelf=a-2-75-stars">a-2-75-stars</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/58882300-valliya-rennell?shelf=b-middle-grade">b-middle-grade</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3458378013" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer5377803572656972231">2.75 stars<br/><br/>The Disney version of <i>Peter Pan</i> was one of my favorite childhood movies. After picking this original, literary version, I found myself very perplexed by the original tale. It isn&apos;t for everyone, and I don&apos;t think I was able to connect with it as much as some other people may, but I appreciated it nonetheless. <b>We follow the Darling siblings, Michael, John, and (mainly) Wendy, as they are whisked off to Neverland by the mysterious boy called Peter Pan, who never wants to grow up.</b> Upon re</span>
  <span id="freeText5377803572656972231" style="display:none">2.75 stars<br /><br />The Disney version of <i>Peter Pan</i> was one of my favorite childhood movies. After picking this original, literary version, I found myself very perplexed by the original tale. It isn't for everyone, and I don't think I was able to connect with it as much as some other people may, but I appreciated it nonetheless. <b>We follow the Darling siblings, Michael, John, and (mainly) Wendy, as they are whisked off to Neverland by the mysterious boy called Peter Pan, who never wants to grow up.</b> Upon reading this book I was amazed at some of the parallels and the importance of the theme of mothers to the story, however I wasn't as impressed by it as little me (or an older me) would have been.<br /><br />This is one of those books where we get a bit of setting, plot, characters, but the major point of the story is themes. I, unfortunately am more of a character reader. Though I thought that Peter was an amazing character, perfectly showing the joy but also heartlessness and selfishness of children (their bipolarity in a sense) <b>I didn't care about him or any of the other characters</b>. Then we have the plot which was fun and heart-warming, but since I wasn't very invested in the characters, <b>I wasn't interested in the plot by proxy</b>. The setting was very interesting, and I loved the way it was presented in the beginning, but since I watched the Disney version so many times, I was kind of desensitised to it. <br /><br />The themes were great, but I didn't really relate to them. Of course I related to the childhood elements, I lived through it not so long ago after all, but I found the themes of motherhood and of that motherly love to be much more prevalent. I am not a mother. I don't know if I <i>want</i> to be a mother. Seeing Wendy, such a young girl, being put into that position made me feel a bit... weird? At this point I've got no clue. I liked Captain Hook, the crocodile, Nana and all the other characters that not only show parallels to other characters but also the connections to the moment in history in which this was made. I did like this book! I thought it was <i>juuust</i> below good (factoring in my enjoyment of it; without enjoyment it would be much higher).<br /><br />I respect this book. Just below 3 stars isn't a bad rating. Unfortunately, despite the wonderful themes, I didn't connect to anything and didn't love my time reading.<br /><br /><i>*book completed as part of the <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/story/show/1303157-year-in-review-2021?chapter=4" rel="nofollow noopener">January Classics challenge</a></i></span>
  <a data-text-id="5377803572656972231" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

<tr class="no_border feedFooterReview" id="update_comment_stuff_Review3458378013">
