<div id="review_3763567686" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3763567686" />
    <a title="Bhavya {on temporary hiatus}" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/128191325-bhavya-on-temporary-hiatus"><img alt="Bhavya {on temporary hiatus}" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1611319656p2/128191325.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3763567686?book_show_action=true">May 24, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Bhavya {on temporary hiatus}" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Bhavya {on temporary hiatus}" href="/user/show/128191325-bhavya-on-temporary-hiatus">Bhavya {on temporary hiatus}</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Audiobook " href="/book/show/16233191-peter-pan">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/128191325-bhavya-on-temporary-hiatus?shelf=audiobooks-i-recommend">audiobooks-i-recommend</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/128191325-bhavya-on-temporary-hiatus?shelf=disappointing-ending">disappointing-ending</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/128191325-bhavya-on-temporary-hiatus?shelf=read-audiobook-2021">read-audiobook-2021</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/128191325-bhavya-on-temporary-hiatus?shelf=read-audiobook">read-audiobook</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/128191325-bhavya-on-temporary-hiatus?shelf=read-2021">read-2021</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/128191325-bhavya-on-temporary-hiatus?shelf=actual-morally-grey-characters">actual-morally-grey-characters</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/128191325-bhavya-on-temporary-hiatus?shelf=classics">classics</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/128191325-bhavya-on-temporary-hiatus?shelf=childrens-books">childrens-books</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/128191325-bhavya-on-temporary-hiatus?shelf=reviewed">reviewed</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/128191325-bhavya-on-temporary-hiatus?shelf=fantasy">fantasy</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3763567686" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9737398358251425969"><i>
  <b>
    <blockquote>“Never say goodbye because goodbye means going away and going away means forgetting.”</blockquote>
  </b>
</i><br/><br/><b>Rating- 2 stars</b><br/><br/><b>Content/ Trigger Warnings-</b> Blood, Death, Racism, Violence<br/><br/><b>-No mention of these in the review-</b><br/><br/><i>Peter Pan</i> is a very well loved book. It is a beloved classic and I was really looking forward to enjoying it, but unfortunately it only left me disappointed.<br/><br/>Unlike most people, I&apos;ve never watched the Disney version of <i>Peter Pan</i>. I don&apos;t have a specific reason as to why, but it never primarily in</span>
  <span id="freeText9737398358251425969" style="display:none"><i>
  <b>
    <blockquote>“Never say goodbye because goodbye means going away and going away means forgetting.”</blockquote>
  </b>
</i><br /><br /><b>Rating- 2 stars</b><br /><br /><b>Content/ Trigger Warnings-</b> Blood, Death, Racism, Violence<br /><br /><b>-No mention of these in the review-</b><br /><br /><i>Peter Pan</i> is a very well loved book. It is a beloved classic and I was really looking forward to enjoying it, but unfortunately it only left me disappointed.<br /><br />Unlike most people, I've never watched the Disney version of <i>Peter Pan</i>. I don't have a specific reason as to why, but it never primarily interested me. Since this book was so appreciated and considered a 'must read', I thought of giving it a try.<br /><br />I sadly didn't enjoy anything about this book, and I have no idea how to 'review' it, as most of the book went over my head.<br /><br />I'm not new to classics or to books with a darker tone, in fact these are the exact books I love reading, so not liking <i>Peter Pan</i> left me very shattered.<br /><br />I can't pinpoint on what exactly I didn't like, but I found the characters bland, the world building confusing and the plot a jumble of several incidents mashed together.<br /><br /><b>Spoiler thoughts:</b> <a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[The fact that Wendy played the role of the 'mother' in this book at such a young age, and the fact that her daughters continue to be Peter's caretaker rubbed me wrong. That was the only thing that I had any strong emotions for as I was indifferent to the rest of the book.  <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span><br /><br />I'm clearly in the minority here, and it pains me to say so, but to me the only redeeming quality of this book was the fact that it was a short read. I do plan on reading it again in the future and am hopeful that my opinion will change.<br /><br /><i>
  <b>
    <blockquote>“Dreams do come true, if only we wish hard enough. You can have anything in life if you will sacrifice everything else for it.”</blockquote>
  </b>
</i><br /><br /><b>Audiobook Comments</b>: The audiobook was narrated by Jim Dale. Fabulous narration. Would highly recommend the audiobook, especially for beginners. <br /> <br /><i>
  <b>
    <blockquote>“All the world is made of faith, and trust, and pixie dust.”</blockquote>
  </b>
</i><br /><br /><b>DISCLAIMER-</b> All opinions on books I’ve read and reviewed are my own, and are with no intention to offend anyone. If you feel offended by my reviews, let me know how I can fix it.<br /><br /><u>How I Rate-</u><br />1 star- Hardly liked anything/ was disappointed<br />2 star- Had potential but did not deliver/ was disappointed<br />3 stars- Was ok but could have been better/ was average / Enjoyed a lot but something was missing<br />4 stars- Loved a lot but something was missing<br />5 stars- Loved it/ new favourite <br /><br /><br />............................................................<br /><br />Pre- review<br /><br /><br />2.5 stars I think. (might change later)<br /><br />The amazing audiobook narration was the only reason I didn’t dnf.<br /><br />Review to come.</span>
  <a data-text-id="9737398358251425969" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


